cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.TL, cs.SE, cs.FL

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is likely because the paper deals with the strong normalization of calculi and the translation of one calculus into another.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is likely because the paper introduces a new calculus with inductive and coinductive types, and discusses call-by-value and call-by-name evaluation strategies.
- cs.TL (Type Theory) is likely because the paper deals with inductive and coinductive types and their reduction rules.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is less likely but still possible because the paper discusses the properties of the introduced calculi, such as strong normalization and Church-Rosser properties.
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is less likely but still possible because the paper deals with the reduction rules of the introduced calculi.
